	dprr:hasID 9059 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7622> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7622" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Pr. 82. See MRR 2.67. Appian's phrase, # (BC 1.88), as T. J. Luce has[112x] shown, does not mean pr. urbanus, but only praetor in or of the city (CPh 56, 1961, 21-28, esp. 22-23). Delete the word urbanus.\n" ;
	dprr:hasID 7622 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4143> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4143" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. Per. 86; Vell. 2.26.2; Val. Max. 9.2.3; App. BC 1.88; Oros. 5.20.4. At the bidding of the Consul Marius, he executed Mucius Scaevola the Pontifex Maximus, Carbo Arvina, L. Domitius, P. Antistius, and other opposing leaders (Cic. Fam. 9.21.2; Rosc. Amer. 90; Sall. Cat. 51.32 and 34; Hist. 1.77.7M; Liv. Per. 86; Vell. 2.26.2; Val. Max. 9.2.3; Plut. Pomp. 9.2-3; App. BC 1.88; Oros. 5.20.4; on Scaevola, see Pontifices). He joined Papirius Carbo in Etruria, aided attempts to relieve Marius in Praeneste, and was killed at Sulla's command after the battle at the Colline Gate (Sall. Cat. 51; App. BC 1.92, cf. 95; Dio 30-35, fr. 109.4)." ;
	dprr:hasID 4143 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4142> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4142" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "3 On the identification of Damasippus, see RE, and Ps.-Acro and Comm. Cruq. on Horace, Sat. 2.3.16ff." ;
	dprr:hasID 4142 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4134> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4134" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A leader of the Marians against Pompey (Plut. Pomp. 7.1-2; cf. Diod. 38.9)." ;
	dprr:hasID 4134 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3945> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3945" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "ILS 8888, listed in fifth place on Pompeius Strabo's staff." ;
	dprr:hasID 3945 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3944> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3944" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "23 Ibid. 141f. The known course of Damasippus' career permits us to identify him with this man, who was probably of quaestorian or tribunician rank in 89." ;
	dprr:hasID 3944 .
